The paper focuses on using deep neural networks for robotic manipulation tasks, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) for feature extraction from video frames suggests that the paper may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN) for sequential generation of output words suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The focus on improving translation accuracy suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of natural language processing techniques for generating output commands suggests that the paper may also belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
